      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHE CAN SOAR (8) relished the step up in trip last time out, racing on the pace then clearing away for an effortless maiden win over 2200m at the Gold Coast. Progressive filly who should enjoy this staying test. PENDING LIST (2) gets over a bit of ground for the first time since joining the Ken Jones stable in April. Won his only race over this trip at Mornington. Hit the line well at Dalby last start and should be at his peak for a race like this. SMELTER (3) kept whacking away to finish fourth over this course and distance in a BM60 a fortnight ago. Just the one win in 29 starts but a top four finish here looks on the cards. PELLINOR (4) ran third in a similar race to this on ANZAC Day and has been tried over shorter trips since. In the mix. MONTEVECCHIO (1) drops back in class and can improve on recent efforts.",
